<div class="col three-sm">
<h3 id="FacilityGroupProxy38812ac03cfb4f2ba06c302e810ef43e-5">Faith services</h3>
<ul class="facility-list clear">
<li class="not-answered">Prayer area <span>(not answered)</span></li>
<li class="not-answered">On-site chapel <span>(not answered)</span></li>
</ul>
<div id="imageContentbf89410d98a54aa8bd763e3c97cb3690">
<div class="profile-pic">
<img alt="Members of the chaplaincy team" border="0" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_column3Content_column3Content_FacilityGroupsRepeater_ctl04_FacilityGroupModule_PhotoView_DisplayImage" src="/Services/UserControls/UploadHandlers/MediaServerHandler.ashx?id=136"/>
</div>
</div>
<p>Hospital chaplains are here for patients, visitors and staff of all faiths as well as those without. Chaplains can support people who have been bereaved; support people with their religious and spiritual beliefs and practices; support people with problems and concerns and provide help in times of crisis. The Royal Hallamshire Hospital chapel is on A floor of the main building and is open from 6am to 9pm. The chapel at Weston Park Hospital is open during the day and is situated on the first floor. The chapel at the Northern General Hospital is situated on the Vickers Corridor. This chapel is open 24 hours a day.A dedicated Muslim prayer room is currently being devel</p>
</div>
